        .row-fluid.speaker
          .span3
            %h2.name= "Hervé Weitz"
            %p.twitter
              =link_to "@weitzh", "http://twitter.com/weitzh"
          .span9.bio
            %p= "Hervé is currently employed at the Interdisciplinary Center for Security, Reliability and Trust (SnT) of the University of Luxembourg as project manager and he is responsible for technologies transfers and spin-off creation."
            %p= "Prior to working at SnT he launched a startup for the development of an intelligent social recommendation engine (thestorybaker.com) and was working as IT consultant for SOGETI."
            %p= "He is also the founder of SELL YOUR MESS an app for easy fast and beautiful selling, buying and renting items. He created the project in spring 2012 and plans to expand the platform to Europe in 2013."
        .row-fluid.abstract
          .span3
          .span9
            %h3= "Sell Your Mess"
            %p= "Luxembourg is not Silicon Valley and never will be, although Luxembourg is unique it has to develop its own formula and its first pioneer consumer technology company."
            %p= "My personal thought was, when it is hard to push a highly innovative and complex product in Luxembourg that should open new markets, why not try with a regarding simple product that disrupts markets. I came up with SELL YOUR MESS, that has even local traditional competitors and the ability to scale beyond the Luxembourgish borders. It is completely trimmed on mobile and social networks, and avoiding similarities to traditional classified ads. It is clearly inspired by Pinterest, Etsy & Instagram, to apply new hype and style to something that exists since the first days of humanity."

        .row-fluid.speaker
          .span3
            %h2.name= "Michael Rupp"
          .span9.bio
            %p= "Michael is part of the development team of our sponsor paymill from munich. He is mainly responsible for their API and everything else that does not need a frontend."
            %p= "Before that he worked on a web based print publishing plattform, got some experience as a freelancer and studied information technologies and mathematics."
            %p= "He loves movies and good food (too much)."
        .row-fluid.abstract
          .span3
          .span9
            %h3= "API - what is that?"
            %p= "Everywhere you hear about cool new APIs you should use nowadays. But what is it? How do i use it? And what do i have to consider if i want to develop one myself?"
            %p= "I will use paymill as an example for an API and discuss the biggest issues when you try to use or to develop something like that."

        .row-fluid.speaker
          .span3
            %h2.name= "Alex Sinner"
            %p.twitter
              =link_to "@alexsinner", "http://twitter.com/alexsinner"
          .span9.bio
            %p.work_title= "Solutions Architect at Amazon Web Services"
            %p= "Alex is a Solutions Architect at Amazon Web Services and works with businesses of all sizes to help them deliver their IT projects in the cloud. During his career Alex has worked as a researcher in Artificial Intelligence, entrepreneur, and in various roles within Amazon.com."
            %p= "Before joining Amazon Web Services, Alex was responsible for the launch of the Amazon marketplace business in Italy and Spain. He uses his experience to help customers bring their ideas to life using Amazon Web Services’ IT infrastructure platform."
        .row-fluid.abstract
          .span3
          .span9
            %h3= "A taste of AWS"

        .row-fluid.speaker
          .span3
            %h2.name= "Rodolfo Baïz"
            %p.twitter
              =link_to "@rod3412", "http://twitter.com/rod3412"
          .span9.bio
            %p= "Fab Lab Manager"
            %p
              =link_to "Rodolfo Baïz on LinkedIn", "http://www.linkedin.com/in/rodolfobaiz"
        .row-fluid.abstract
